counter serves as the public registry for new arrivals. Cork boards

cover every available wall surface with notices of varying age: work

postings, missing-person notices, room-letting announcements, and

official proclamations from the Compact. A clerk behind the counter

offers a stamped entry record and a brief orientation for first-time

visitors. Two wide-eyed newcomers study the boards with the focused

attention of people determined not to look lost.@@N

